    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix get_default_ue_id() always returns -1 in telnet server\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_default_ue_id()` function in the telnet server implementation always returns -1 because it only checks for RRC instance 0, which may not be initialized. This causes telnet commands that rely on default UE ID to fail.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Start OAI 5G nrUE with a non-zero instance ID\n2. Connect to telnet server\n3. Try any command that uses default UE ID (e.g., \"add_pdu_session 1\")\n4. Observe error message \"No default UE context found\"\n\n### Root Cause\nThe function `get_default_ue_id()` in `telnetsrv_ciUE.c` hardcodes the instance to 0:\n```c\nNR_UE_RRC_INST_t *rrc = get_NR_UE_rrc_inst(0);\n```\nWhen UE is initialized with a different instance ID (e.g., 1, 2, etc.), this check fails and returns -1 even when valid UE instances exist.\n\n### Impact\nAll telnet commands that rely on automatic UE ID detection fail, requiring users to manually specify UE IDs even when only one UE is active.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/telnetsrv/telnetsrv_ciUE.c`: Modified `get_default_ue_id()` to search through all possible UE instances (0 to MAX_NUM_NR_UE_INST-1) and return the first available one\n- Added required header include for MAX_NUM_NR_UE_INST definition\n\n"
}